I"Q<p>This is how I edit videos of talks that I need to incorporate slides and video together</p>

<p>I’m on a Mac</p>

<ul>
  <li>import to iMovie (using v10 something)</li>
  <li>drop movie into editing section</li>
  <li>split pdf slides into individual files <code class="highlighter-rouge">pdfseparate foobar.pdf %d.pdf</code></li>
  <li>convert individual pdf slides into png <code class="highlighter-rouge">sips -s format png --out "${pdf%%.*}.png" "$pdf"</code></li>
  <li>import png’s into imovie</li>
  <li>for each image, drop into editing area where you want it</li>
  <li>when focused on the png of the slide:
    <ul>
      <li>select crop, then - choose <code class="highlighter-rouge">fit</code>, say okay</li>
      <li>select “add as overlay” (very most left symbol), then choose <code class="highlighter-rouge">picture in picture</code></li>
      <li>then choose <code class="highlighter-rouge">swap</code></li>
      <li>then move inset to where you want it</li>
      <li>say okay</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>rinse and repeat for all slides</li>
  <li>export - via <code class="highlighter-rouge">File</code> option</li>
  <li>share to youtube</li>
</ul>

